Package LMS.entities

Class InterationalDelivery

  • Object
    • LMS.entities.Delivery
      • LMS.entities.InterationalDelivery
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Comparable<Delivery>
    public class InterationalDelivery
extends Delivery
    An international delivery within the Logistics Management System.

    For international deliveries a factor can be set that is used to calculate customs when crossing borders.

    This factor is applied to the goods' total value when calculating the total of an international delivery.

      • InterationalDelivery

        public InterationalDelivery​(long id,
                            String from,
                            String to,
                            float custom)
        Constructs an international delivery with specified id,custom factor, pickup and drop off location.

        The id must be greater than 0 and the custom factor must be greater than or equal to 1.

        If the id is invalid an IllegalArgumentException is thrown. An invalid custom factor is ignored and instead set to 1.

        Parameters:
        id - the id to set
        from - the pick up location to set
        to - the drop off location to set
        custom - the custom factor to set
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - when invalid arguments are passed

    • Method Detail

      • getTotal

        public int getTotal()
        Calculates the total amount (of money) to be collected at the drop off location in Euro cents.

        The total amount to be collected is the combined total value of all shipping items in this delivery multiplied by the customs factor. If this delivery contains no shipping items -1 is returned.

        Specified by:
        getTotal in class Delivery
        Returns:
        the total amount of money to be collected at the drop off location in Euro cents, or -1 if this delivery contains no shipping items.

        Delivery.getTotal()
